EFF leader Julius Malema eNCA JOHANNESBURG - EFF leader Julius Malema is back in court. Malema faces charges related to discharging a firearm in public. He was caught on camera apparently firing an assault rifle at his party's fifth birthday celebrations. READ: Malema: AfriForum's Roets not an expert on the EFF The event was held at the Sisa Dukashe Stadium in Mdansane in 2018. Malema faces charges of illegal possession of a firearm and ammunition. He also faces charges of reckless endangerment to persons or property.